    "kicker": "24 June 2026",
    "dek": "The day a windless Britain leaned on its neighbours \u2014 until they pulled the plug.",
    "body_md": "A blocking high sat over north-west Europe and the wind fell away across the whole region at once. Through the morning Britain leaned hard on imports; by the evening peak, with demand high and the wind still flat, our neighbours kept their scarce power for themselves \u2014 and the system operator paid for emergency generation to keep the lights on. Press the play button and watch the day unfold.",
